-righteousness-al-birr","tag-fasting-al-siyam","tag-shahr-al-muharram","tag-night-prayer-al-tahajjud","tag-night-al-layl","tag-obligations-faraid","tag-prayer-al-salat","tag-ramadan","tag-virtue-al-fadail","tag-voluntary-prayers-salat-nafilah","tag-worship-al-ibadah"],"aioseo_notices":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p95VHY-qt","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":35803,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/04\/27\/ali-khutbah-ramadan\/","url_meta":{"origin":1641,"position":0},"title":"Ali on Ramadan: Sermon given at the arrival of Ramadan","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 27, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Sha\u2019bi reported: Ali, may Allah be pleased with him, would deliver a sermon when the month of Ramadan arrived, saying, \u201cThis is the blessed month in which Allah has obligated fasting and not obligated night prayers. Certainly, fasting is not merely from food and drink, but rather from lying, falsehood,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":28113,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/04\/26\/sawm-9th-muharram-ashura\/","url_meta":{"origin":1641,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on &#8216;Ashura: Fasting 9th of Muharram with &#8216;Ashura","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 26, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Abbas reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cIf I live until next year, I will certainly fast the ninth day of al-Muharram.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1134 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim Imam Ibn Hajar commented, \u201cThe fast of 'Ashura has three\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":24945,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/06\/05\/fast-ramadan-sins-forgiven\/","url_meta":{"origin":1641,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Ramadan: Whoever fasts Ramadan will have his sins forgiven","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 5, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdur Rahman ibn Awf reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, Ramadan is a month in which Allah Almighty has obligated its fasting. I have instituted for Muslims the practice of prayer at night. Thus, whoever fasts it with faith and expecting reward will\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33326,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/08\/31\/fasting-ashura-9th-muharram\/","url_meta":{"origin":1641,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on &#8216;Ashura: Fasting day of &#8216;Ashura with 9th of Muharram","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 31, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Hakam ibn al-A\u2019raj reported: I went to Ibn Abbas, may Allah be pleased with him, and I said, \u201cTell me about fasting the day of 'Ashura.\u201d Ibn Abbas said, \u201cWhen you see the crescent of the month of al-Muharram, count the days and wake up to fast on the ninth\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\